From baa52141636af52cd8ddc5b4230299728ae4215b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Thu, 8 May 2025 11:37:26 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:wifi: ath12k Add NL vendor command to support Airtime fairness

Define subcmd QCA_NL80211_VENDOR_SUBCMD_ATF_OFFLOAD_OPS
with ID 261 for Airtime Fairness (ATF).

Add QCA vendor command and attributes for Airtime Fairness (ATF)
offload operations. This command enables configuration and control of ATF
features, which aim to ensure fair scheduling of wireless medium
access from the Access Point (AP) and optimize overall Wi-Fi bandwidth
utilization.

This interface is intended for use to dynamically manage airtime
distribution based on scheduling policy (if configured) across various
entities such as SSIDs,SSID groups, peers, and access categories.

Patch-dependency: a016-001-QSDK-CP-WMI-changes-for-ATF.patch
Patch-work: None

Signed-off-by: Harish Rachakonda <rachakon@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
